criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients seeking dental treatment at the School of Dentistry;

          -  Age between 18 and 60 years;

          -  Patients who present at least one restoration of composite resin or amalgam to
             posterior and/or anterior teeth.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who refuse to participate in the research;

          -  Patients included in other surveys that involve restorations or are in systematic
             attendance at another clinic or service;

          -  Patients who present systemic conditions or chronic diseases that require
             differentiated care and follow-up - these will be referred to the specific services
             available at the Faculty of Dentistry;

          -  Patients who reside in other locations and who can not return for periodic follow-up
             of the interventions.
